<exercise xml:id="PP-efbfe3dbfd3d4045" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
<!-- ============================================ 
  Problema de práctica                            
=================================================  -->

<!-- <title>Previo a la unidad</title> -->
<!-- <title>Exploración</title> -->
<!-- <title component="metadata">Alineado con <xref ref="graVV-uniYY-secZZ" text="title"/></title> -->
<title component="metadata">Alineado con <xref ref="lec-VVVVVV" text="title"/></title>

<statement>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>Tyler hizo este dibujo y dijo que <m>\frac{3}{4}</m> es equivalente a <m>\frac{2}{3}</m>. Explica por qué Tyler no tiene razón.</p>
      <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-151751">
        <shortdescription>2 number lines. First, 0 to 2 thirds by thirds, unevenly spaced tick marks. Second, 0 to 3 fourths by fourths, unevenly spaced tick marks.</shortdescription>
      </image>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Encuentra una fracción equivalente a <m>\frac{2}{3}</m> .</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Encuentra una fracción equivalente a <m>\frac{3}{4}</m> .</p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</statement>

<solution>
  <p>[++++++++++++++++++++]</p>
  <p>Sample responses:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>Tyler's number lines are not accurate. His thirds are not equally spaced. His fourths are also not equally spaced.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><m>\frac{2}{3}</m> is equivalent to <m>\frac{4}{6}</m> .</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><m>\frac{3}{4}</m> is equivalent to <m>\frac{6}{8}</m> .</p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</solution>

</exercise>
